import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import tensorflow as tf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from tensorflow.keras.layers import LSTM, Dense
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler

temps = newdf["AvgTemperature"].values.astype("float32")

# Normalize data
scaler = MinMaxScaler()
temps_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(temps.reshape(-1, 1)).flatten()

# Set sequence length (timesteps)
sequence_length = 2  # Model will look at 14 previous days

# Create sequences
X, y = [], []
for i in range(len(temps_scaled) - sequence_length):
    X.append(temps_scaled[i:i + sequence_length])
    y.append(temps_scaled[i + sequence_length])
X = np.array(X)
y = np.array(y)
# X.shape[0] is number of samples 
# sequence_length is number of timestep
# 1 is numnber of features (avg temp that day)
X = X.reshape((X.shape[0], sequence_length, 1))  # shape: (samples, timesteps, features)

# Split into train and test sets (e.g., 80% train, 20% test)
split_index = int(len(X) * 0.8)
X_train, X_test = X[:split_index], X[split_index:]
y_train, y_test = y[:split_index], y[split_index:]

# 2. Define the model
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.InputLayer(shape=(sequence_length, 1)),
    tf.keras.layers.LSTM(50, activation='relu'),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(1)
])

# 3. Compile and train
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mse')
model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=100, verbose=1, validation_split=0.1)


# 4. Predict on test set
y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
y_pred_rescaled = scaler.inverse_transform(y_pred)
y_test_rescaled = scaler.inverse_transform(y_test.reshape(-1, 1))

# 5. Plot predicted vs true temperatures
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
plt.plot(y_test_rescaled, label="True Temp")
plt.plot(y_pred_rescaled, label="Predicted Temp")
plt.xlabel("Days")
plt.ylabel("Avg Temperature (°C)")
plt.title("LSTM Weather Forecast - Algiers")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 6. Predict next day after the last 7 days
last_seq = temps_scaled[-sequence_length:].reshape((1, sequence_length, 1))
next_day_pred_scaled = model.predict(last_seq)
next_day_pred = scaler.inverse_transform(next_day_pred_scaled)
print("Predicted next day's temperature:", round(next_day_pred[0][0], 2), "°C")

LSTM with 3 hidden layers (2 LSTM layers)¶

In [86]:
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import tensorflow as tf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from tensorflow.keras.layers import LSTM, Dense
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler

temps = newdf["AvgTemperature"].values.astype("float32")

# Normalize data
scaler = MinMaxScaler()
temps_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(temps.reshape(-1, 1)).flatten()

# Set sequence length (timesteps)
sequence_length = 2  # Model will look at 14 previous days

# Create sequences
X, y = [], []
for i in range(len(temps_scaled) - sequence_length):
    X.append(temps_scaled[i:i + sequence_length])
    y.append(temps_scaled[i + sequence_length])
X = np.array(X)
y = np.array(y)
# X.shape[0] is number of samples 
# sequence_length is number of timestep
# 1 is numnber of features (avg temp that day)
X = X.reshape((X.shape[0], sequence_length, 1))  # shape: (samples, timesteps, features)

# Split into train and test sets (e.g., 80% train, 20% test)
split_index = int(len(X) * 0.8)
X_train, X_test = X[:split_index], X[split_index:]
y_train, y_test = y[:split_index], y[split_index:]

# 2. Define the model
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.InputLayer(shape=(sequence_length, 1)),
    tf.keras.layers.LSTM(64, return_sequences=True),  # Send full sequence to next LSTM
    tf.keras.layers.LSTM(32),                         # Output: last hidden state
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(1)                          # Final prediction
])


# 3. Compile and train
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mse')
model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=100, verbose=1, validation_split=0.1)


# 4. Predict on test set
y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
y_pred_rescaled = scaler.inverse_transform(y_pred)
y_test_rescaled = scaler.inverse_transform(y_test.reshape(-1, 1))

# 5. Plot predicted vs true temperatures
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
plt.plot(y_test_rescaled, label="True Temp")
plt.plot(y_pred_rescaled, label="Predicted Temp")
plt.xlabel("Days")
plt.ylabel("Avg Temperature (°C)")
plt.title("LSTM Weather Forecast - Algiers")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 6. Predict next day after the last 7 days
last_seq = temps_scaled[-sequence_length:].reshape((1, sequence_length, 1))
next_day_pred_scaled = model.predict(last_seq)
next_day_pred = scaler.inverse_transform(next_day_pred_scaled)
print("Predicted next day's temperature:", round(next_day_pred[0][0], 2), "°C")

GRU¶

The only part that changes with respect to LSTM is change the type of hidden layers which are LSTM to GRU:¶

```python model = tf.keras.Sequential([ tf.keras.layers.InputLayer(input_shape=(sequence_length, 1)), # Input layer tf.keras.layers.GRU(64, return_sequences=True), # First GRU layer tf.keras.layers.GRU(32), # Second GRU layer tf.keras.layers.Dense(1) # Output layer ])

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import tensorflow as tf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from tensorflow.keras.layers import GRU, Dense
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler

# 1. Extract temperature data
temps = newdf["AvgTemperature"].values.astype("float32")

# 2. Normalize data
scaler = MinMaxScaler()
temps_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(temps.reshape(-1, 1)).flatten()

# 3. Set sequence length
sequence_length = 2  # number of previous days used to predict the next day

# 4. Create sequences
X, y = [], []
for i in range(len(temps_scaled) - sequence_length):
    X.append(temps_scaled[i:i + sequence_length])
    y.append(temps_scaled[i + sequence_length])
X = np.array(X)
y = np.array(y)
X = X.reshape((X.shape[0], sequence_length, 1))  # shape = (samples, timesteps, features)

# 5. Train/test split
split_index = int(len(X) * 0.8)
X_train, X_test = X[:split_index], X[split_index:]
y_train, y_test = y[:split_index], y[split_index:]

# 6. Define the GRU model
model = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.InputLayer(shape=(sequence_length, 1)),
    tf.keras.layers.GRU(64, return_sequences=True),  # First GRU layer
    tf.keras.layers.GRU(32),                         # Second GRU layer
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(1)                         # Output layer
])

# 7. Compile and train
model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mse')
model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=100, verbose=1, validation_split=0.1)

# 8. Predict on test set
y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
y_pred_rescaled = scaler.inverse_transform(y_pred)
y_test_rescaled = scaler.inverse_transform(y_test.reshape(-1, 1))

# 9. Plot results
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
plt.plot(y_test_rescaled, label="True Temp")
plt.plot(y_pred_rescaled, label="Predicted Temp")
plt.xlabel("Days")
plt.ylabel("Avg Temperature (°C)")
plt.title("GRU Weather Forecast - Algiers")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 10. Predict the next day after last known sequence
last_seq = temps_scaled[-sequence_length:].reshape((1, sequence_length, 1))
next_day_pred_scaled = model.predict(last_seq)
next_day_pred = scaler.inverse_transform(next_day_pred_scaled)
print("Predicted next day's temperature:", round(next_day_pred[0][0], 2), "°C")
